<topic id='element_organisation_code__residence_responsibility_.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Data Element: ORGANISATION CODE (RESIDENCE RESPONSIBILITY) - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
    <dl>
      <dlentry>
        <dt>Format / Length</dt>
        <dd>an3</dd>
      </dlentry>
    </dl>

  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_organisation_code__residence_responsibility_">ORGANISATION CODE (RESIDENCE RESPONSIBILITY)</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_organisation_code">ORGANISATION CODE</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_organisation_code__residence_responsibility_">ORGANISATION CODE (RESIDENCE RESPONSIBILITY)</xref>
 is the 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_organisation_code">ORGANISATION CODE</xref>
 derived from the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
's 
    <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_postcode_of_usual_address">POSTCODE OF USUAL ADDRESS</xref>
, where they reside within the boundary of a:  </p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_clinical_commissioning_group">Clinical Commissioning Group</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_care_trust">Care Trust</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_local_health_board__wales_">Local Health Board (Wales)</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_scottish_health_board">Scottish Health Board</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_northern_ireland_local_commissioning_group">Northern Ireland Local Commissioning Group</xref>
            <p>
: 
                <i>
Guidance on the use of Northern Ireland codes can be found in 
                  <xref href="https://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/+/http://www.isb.nhs.uk/library_old/dscn//dscn2009/dataset/192009.pdf"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">Data Set Change Notice 19/2009</xref>
               </i>
            </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_primary_healthcare_directorate__isle_of_man_">Primary Healthcare Directorate (Isle of Man)</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_local_authority">Local Authority</xref>
            <p>.</p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_organisation_code">ORGANISATION CODES</xref>
 can be downloaded from 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/technology_reference_data_update_distribution_(trud).asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Technology_Reference_Data_Update_Distribution_(TRUD)</xref>
. For further information, see 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/organisation_data_service.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Organisation_Data_Service</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
For 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 who are 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_overseas_visitor">Overseas Visitors</xref>
: 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/organisation_data_service_default_codes.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Organisation Data Service Default Code</xref>
 X98 '
    <i>Primary Care Organisation Not Applicable (</i>
      <i>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_overseas_visitor">Overseas Visitors</xref>
      </i>
 )' should be reported. 
    <i>
Note: A review of 
      <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/organisation_data_service_default_codes.asp"
               scope="external"
               format="html">Organisation_Data_Service_Default_Codes</xref>
 is planned to be carried out and this default code will be updated as part of that.    </i>
  </p>
  <p>
For the purposes of sending Commissioning Data Set messages to the 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/secondary_uses_service.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Secondary_Uses_Service</xref>
 (regardless of how local systems hold the data), it is essential at present to continue using a 3 character field, using the first 3 characters of the 
    <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_organisation_code__residence_responsibility_">ORGANISATION CODE (RESIDENCE RESPONSIBILITY)</xref>
 and following the same update rules relating to Prime Recipient as are currently in place. This is necessary, primarily to preserve the integrity of the current Commissioning Data Set message and the 
    <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_cds_prime_recipient_identity">CDS PRIME RECIPIENT IDENTITY</xref>
 which is derived from the 
    <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_organisation_code__residence_responsibility_">ORGANISATION CODE (RESIDENCE RESPONSIBILITY)</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/organisation_data_service.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Organisation_Data_Service</xref>
 provides postcode files which link postcodes to the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_clinical_commissioning_group">Clinical Commissioning Group</xref>
. See 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/nhs_postcode_directory.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">NHS_Postcode_Directory</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <b>
         <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_organisation_code__residence_responsibility_">ORGANISATION CODE (RESIDENCE RESPONSIBILITY)</xref>
 will be replaced with 
      <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_organisation_identifier__residence_responsibility_">ORGANISATION IDENTIFIER (RESIDENCE RESPONSIBILITY)</xref>
, when it has been approved for use in national information standards.    </b>
  </p>


